/node_modules/
# Local-only Claude Code context (testing workflow + repo conventions).
# This is a public repo; the file may reference paths and host names
# from the maintainer's setup that don't belong on GitHub.
CLAUDE.md
# rollup-plugin-copy reuses the dist/ tree across runs but never
# regenerates .gz on its own — those are leftovers from local pushes
# to a Home Assistant instance and should never be committed.
dist/*.gz
# Sourcemaps emitted only by `npm run bundle:analyze` for one-off
# bundle attribution. Never ship them — terser-mangled prod bundle
# stays opaque on the wire.
dist/*.map
# Local-only research / calibration scratchpad. Issue-comment drafts,
# data dumps, calibration scripts. Each release iteration leaves a few
# files here that aren't part of the shipped card.
scratch/
# Playwright run artifacts. Visual-regression baselines under
# tests-e2e/snapshots/ ARE committed (they're the contract the
# suite checks against); per-run output below is not.
test-results/
playwright-report/
.playwright/
# Most of .claude/ is local-only (scheduled_tasks.lock, settings.local.json),
# but skills/ and the project-wide settings.json (PreToolUse hook for the
# commit-guardian skill) are checked in so every contributor — human or AI —
# gets the same pre-commit ADR check.
.claude/*
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/settings.json
# Coverage output — generated per-run by `vitest run --coverage`,
# consumed by SonarCloud (when activated) via coverage/lcov.info.
coverage/
# Throwaway helper scripts used during a single editing session
# (e.g. ESLint violation extractors during a sweep). Never shipped.
.tmp-*
# Phase artifacts from the AI workflow (~/.claude/skills/{brainstorm,grill-me,
# plan-vertical,recap,verify-fix}). Transient — cleared at end of each task.
.workflow/
